//http://www.dbforums.com/showthread.php?1707382-Compare-avg-of-data-in-column-of-certain-users-against-a-another-user

#input

| trans | user:Str | Month |
|----------------------| 
| 100   |  1   |    1  | 
| 102   |  2   |    1  | 
| 103   |  3   |    1  | 
| 100   |  1   |    2  | 
| 103   |  2   |    2  | 
| 103   |  3   |    2  | 
| 104   |  1   |    3  | 
| 104   |  2   |    3  | 
| 101   |  3   |    3  |

#output

| Avgtrans | user3Trans | Month |
|-------------------------------|
| 101      |      103   |   1   |
| 101.5    |      103   |   2   |
| 104      |      101   |   3   |

#constraint
{
	"constants": ["3:Str"],
	"aggregation_functions": ["avg"]
}

#solution

```sql
SELECT
    T1.avg_trans,
    T0.trans,
    T1.Month 
FROM
    input1 AS T0 
JOIN
    (
        SELECT
            Month,
            avg(trans) AS avg_trans 
        FROM
            input1 
        WHERE
            user <> '3' 
        GROUP BY
            Month
    ) AS T1 
        ON T1.Month = T0.Month 
WHERE
    T0.user = '3' 
ORDER BY
    T0.trans DESC
```

```sql
select Avgtrans, t2.trans, t1.month
from 
(select month, avg(trans) Avgtrans
 from t
 having user <> 3
 groupy month) t1
join
(select *
 from t
 where user = 3) t2
on t1.month = t2.month
```
